  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Global industrial policy advice facility for the inclusive and sustainable transformation of industries</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">This concept note answers a request from the Deutsche Gesellschaft f&#xFC;r Internationale Zusammenarbeit (GIZ) GmbH received on 6 August 2021 for submitting a proposal to establish a global facility for providing industrial policy advice to developing countries.  This project implements the establishment and piloting of such facility. Thereby, it responds to requests for policy support UNIDO received over the years that the Organization had to reject because these requests were too small to be practically handled by the organization. The facility aims at functioning as a to-go-place for governments, regional and subregional entities in developing countries that need a rapid response, and quick and short-term industrial policy advice.  The purpose of this project is to pilot a facility which aims at providing developing countries, globally, with sound policy advice for the sustainable and inclusive transformation of industries. The facility does so through the provision of direct advisory work covering the entire policy cycle, and indirectly through knowledge products such as policy studies and briefs; compilation and mainstreaming lessons learned and best practices, capacity development and training; and awareness making activities. Apart from direct interaction, the facility makes use of innovative communication t</narrative>
  </description>
